In [[Islam]]ic tradition, '''Haizum''' ({{lang-ar|حيزوم}}) is the horse of the archangel [[Gabriel]]. It is a white, flaming, spiritual horse that has wings like that of a [[pegasus]] and can fly swiftly from one cosmic plane to another in a second. Haizum was [[God]]'s gift to Gabriel for pleasing Him.

A legend based on sura [[Ta-Ha]], 96 relates that dust from Haizum’s hoofprints was thrown the [[golden calf]]’s mouth.

It is mentioned in [[Sahih Muslim]] that [[Abd Allah ibn Abbas]] said: "While on that day a Muslim from the [[ansar (military)|Ansar]] was chasing a [[kafir|disbeliever]], he heard over him the swashing of a whip and the voice of the rider saying: 'Go ahead Haizum.' He looked at the disbelievers who had fell on the ground on his back. The man came to Allah's Messenger (sallallahu alaihe wa-sallam) and related the incident, upon which Allah's Messenger (sallallahu alaihe wa-sallam) said: "You have told the truth. This was the help from the [[Third Heaven#Islam|third Heaven]]."<ref>https://sunnah.com/muslim/32/69</ref>

